eclipse ide download link
=========================
https://www.eclipse.org/downloads/




tomcat server download link
===========================
https://tomcat.apache.org/download-90.cgi

============================================
*   after installing the tomcat server add the bin folder path in environment variables under path section

edit the port
Open conf folder  -- >  open  server.xml file  in a text editor.

Find this line (usually around line 69):


<Connector port="8080" protocol="HTTP/1.1"
           connectionTimeout="20000"
           redirectPort="8443" />

Change the port number from 8080 to another number (e.g., 9090):


<Connector port="9090" protocol="HTTP/1.1"
           connectionTimeout="20000"
           redirectPort="8443" />


Step 3: Save and restart Tomcat
Save the file.

Restart your Tomcat server.

Now, your application will run at http://localhost:9090 instead of http://localhost:8080.*    

=================================================================================================
how to integrate tomcat server with eclipse how?


Apache Tomcat downloaded (e.g., Tomcat 9 or 10)
ðŸ‘‰ Download from: https://tomcat.apache.org

âœ… Step 1: Download and Extract Apache Tomcat
Go to https://tomcat.apache.org

Click on Tomcat 9 (or any version you want)

Download the .zip version for Windows

Extract the ZIP file to a location like:


C:\apache-tomcat-9.x.x
âœ… Step 2: Configure Tomcat in Eclipse/STS
Open Eclipse or Spring Tool Suite (STS)

Go to the menu:
Window > Preferences

Expand:


Server > Runtime Environments
Click Addâ€¦

Choose:


Apache > Apache Tomcat v9.0 (or your version)
Click Next

Browse to the location where you extracted Tomcat, e.g.:


C:\apache-tomcat-9.0.x
Click Finish
